00:00:05.042 --> 00:00:06.801
and it's like, which one?

00:00:06.802 --> 00:00:08.801
It worked pretty much everywhere.

00:00:08.802 --> 00:00:10.361
Not Cambodia and some parts of Eastern Europe

00:00:10.362 --> 00:00:11.281
because they weren't really social.

00:00:11.282 --> 00:00:14.641
But the point is that it was working for poor people

00:00:14.642 --> 00:00:16.461
and colonized people.

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:17.920
That's why the United States

00:00:17.921 --> 00:00:21.481
through everything it had at socialism during the Cold War,

00:00:21.482 --> 00:00:24.501
to try to keep it from continuing to work.

00:00:24.600 --> 00:00:26.800
If socialism doesn't work,

00:00:26.801 --> 00:00:30.201
then why does the United States have to keep fighting it all the time?

00:00:30.202 --> 00:00:33.321
It works at taking their colonial property back

00:00:33.322 --> 00:00:36.261
and actually giving it to the people who work and live there.

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:37.240
That's the whole point.

00:00:37.241 --> 00:00:38.361
That's the big

00:00:38.362 --> 00:00:41.601
evil socialism that the government has been trying to scare you with

00:00:41.602 --> 00:00:44.401
since they put it in your curriculums in school.

00:00:44.402 --> 00:00:48.281
Every country where socialism was attempted started dirt poor,

00:00:48.282 --> 00:00:50.441
war torn, or colonized.

00:00:50.442 --> 00:00:51.941
And then these people,

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:54.000
these Westerners,

00:00:54.001 --> 00:00:57.721
tell you to compare them to the rich, colonizer,

00:00:57.722 --> 00:00:59.441
war mongering countries.

00:00:59.442 --> 00:01:00.481
It's ridiculous.

00:01:00.482 --> 00:01:03.921
